              <ol>
                <li>
                  Read Reviews and Get Quotes: Visit websites to read reviews
                  and get multiple quotes for both repair and replacement
                  options. This will give you a range of costs to consider.
                </li>
                <li>
                  Warranty and Coverage: Verify if your dryer is still under
                  warranty. Sometimes, repairs can be covered, making it more
                  economical to fix rather than replace.
